		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Orraaaaa! The platforms are now memory mapped in zero page as pointers! (YESSSSSS)<br /><br /><img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DUa7E6xWsAE2nvl.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Also, for NROM 256, surely my filesize should be 40kb, not 49kb?<br /><br />Orr have I missed something?<br /><br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;PRG ROM:&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 x 16KiB<br />&nbsp;CHR ROM:&nbsp; &nbsp; 1 x&nbsp; 8KiB<br />&nbsp;ROM CRC32:&nbsp; 0x5ddeb4ae<br />&nbsp;ROM MD5:&nbsp; 0xf67bcc4f6cf62b95cb3fde08520e7a41<br />&nbsp;Mapper #:&nbsp; 0<br />&nbsp;Mapper name: NROM<br />&nbsp;Mirroring: Vertical<br />&nbsp;Battery-backed: No<br />&nbsp;Trained: No</div><br /><br />[edit]<br />Fixed it, just removed the last 8192 characters from the file and resaved, apparently windows 7 always rounds up<br />[/edit]

		

